  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>App Name:</strong> Nexora From Cad to Revit</p>
  <p><strong>Publisher:</strong> NEXORA</p>
  <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> May 2026</p>

  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>NEXORA is committed to protecting the privacy of users of the Nexora From Cad to Revit add-in for Autodesk Revit. This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and your rights as a user.</p>

  <h2>2. Data Collection</h2>
  <p>The Nexora From Cad to Revit add-in does <strong>not</strong> collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data or user information. All operations — including CAD geometry detection and Revit element creation — are executed locally on your machine within the Autodesk Revit environment. No project data, element information, or file contents are ever transmitted outside of Revit.</p>

  <h2>3. Tools Included</h2>
  <p>This add-in includes the following tools:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Isolated Footings</strong> — Automatically detect and create isolated footings from CAD drawings.</li>
    <li><strong>Circular Columns</strong> — Detect circles from CAD and create circular structural columns.</li>
    <li><strong>Rectangle Columns</strong> — Detect rectangles from CAD and create rectangular structural columns.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>This add-in does not integrate with any third-party analytics, advertising, or data collection services.</p>

  <h2>5. Internet Access</h2>
  <p>The Nexora From Cad to Revit add-in does not require or use an internet connection. No data is sent to external servers.</p>

  <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated date.</p>

  <h2>7. Contact</h2>
